node.title: Fire crews back on the scene at Trentham
node.description: Fire and Emergency said operations will ramp up again this morning.
node.content: ["Fire crews are attempting to make the most of cooler morning conditions in Wellington to mop up the fire at Trentham, in Upper Hutt.", "The blaze, at Evergreen Crescent, was under control shortly after 5pm yesterday but ground crews remained at the scene overnight.", "About 14 hectares of land has been burnt.", "Fire and Emergency said operations will ramp up again this morning.", "Helicopters started operating at 6.15am while ground crews are working beside Rimutaka Prison and off the top of Chatsworth Road.", "Residents in Trentham and Silverstream are being warned smoke may be visible in the area over the next few days.", "Fire and Emergency says anyone who is affected by the smoke, particularly downwind of the fire, should keep their doors and windows closed and call healthline if they need medical advice.", "RNZ"]
